HEADWORD: Japanner
<hw>Ja*pan"ner</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
varnishes in the manner of the Japanese, or one skilled in the
art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bootblack.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Japanning</ent>⟦br⟧
